==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acception
<hw>Ac*cep"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acceptio</ets> a receiving, accepting: cf. F.
<ets>acception</ets>.]</ety> <def>Acceptation; the received
meaning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here the word ⟦ldquo⟧baron⟦rdquo⟧ is not to be taken in that
restrictive sense to which the modern <qex>acception</qex> hath confined
it.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Acception of persons</b></col> or
<col><b>faces</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>, <cd>favoritism;
partiality.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acceptive</ent>⟦br⟧
